headlines.description: — Marcus Morris Sr. threw a high, intentional elbow that flattened one of the Hornets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Evan Mobley scores 17 as Cavaliers respond after Morris elbow, ejection and handle Hornets 115-92

headlines.description: — De’Andre Hunter could’ve held the ball and forced the Celtics to foul.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks rally from 30 points down to stun NBA-leading Celtics 120-118

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Donte DiVincenzo was on the verge of history and in a hurry to get there.
headlines.shortLinkText: DiVincenzo makes franchise-record 11 3-pointers, scores 40 points as Knicks rout Pistons 124-99

headlines.description: — Dennis Schroder scored 19 points against his former team, Trendon Watford had 11 of his season-high 19 points in the second quarter and the Brooklyn Nets snapped a six-game losing streak by beating the short-handed Toronto Raptors 96-88 on Monday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Schroder, Watford score 19 apiece, Nets beat Raptors 96-88 to snap 6-game skid

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored 23 points and the Washington Wizards won their season-high third straight game, beating the Chicago Bulls 107-105 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole scores 23 as Wizards beat Bulls 107-105 for season-high 3rd straight win

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 27 points to lead the Houston Rockets to a 110-92 win over the Portland Trail Blazers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green’s 27 points leads Rockets over Trail Blazers for 9th straight win

events.name: Phoenix Suns at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jeremy Sochan hit a key 3-pointer in the final minute and finished with 26 points and a career-high 18 rebounds as San Antonio beat the Phoenix Suns 104-102 on Monday night with Spurs rookie Victor Wembanyama sidelined due to injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sochan, Vassell lead Spurs past Suns 104-102 as injured Wembanyama watches from sidelines

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 29 points, 11 rebounds and eight assists, Christian Braun scored 17 and the Denver Nuggets beat the Memphis Grizzlies 128-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 29, Western Conference-leading Nuggets beat Grizzlies 128-103

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 29 points, 13 assists, and 12 rebounds to help the Dallas Mavericks beat the Utah Jazz 115-105 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic gets triple-double as Mavericks beat Jazz 115-105

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had his NBA-leading 25th triple-double of the season on a milestone night, leading the Sacramento Kings to a 108-96 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis' milestone night helps the Kings beat the 76ers 108-96

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 31 points to lead the Indiana Pacers to a 133-116 win over the Los Angeles Clippers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam helps Pacers pull away from Clippers for 133-116 win
